  "translations": {
    "en": "So Allah, Blessed and Exalted, revealed to His Prophet (peace be upon him and his family): 'And those who, when they commit an indecency' — meaning fornication — 'or wrong themselves' — meaning by committing a sin greater than fornication, grave robbing, and taking shrouds — 'remember Allah and seek forgiveness for their sins' — meaning they feared Allah and hastened to repent — 'and who can forgive sins except Allah?' He said, Mighty and Majestic: My servant came to you repentant, O Muhammad, and you sent him away. Where would he go, to whom would he turn, and whom would he ask to forgive his sin besides Me? Then He said, Mighty and Majestic: 'and those who do not persist in what they have done while they know' — meaning they no longer commit fornication, grave robbing, or taking shrouds — 'their reward is forgiveness from their Lord and gardens beneath which rivers flow, wherein they shall abide eternally, and excellent is the reward of the doers of good' (3:135-136).",
